    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-09-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <head>127. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d127fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751K.00/9-561. Official Use Only; Priority. Repeated to Bangkok,
                        Phnom Penh, Vientiane, <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for
                            <gloss target="#t_PolAd1">PolAd</gloss>, London, Paris, and Geneva for
                            <gloss target="#t_FECON1">FECON</gloss>. The Department of State was
                        also asked to pass a copy to ACSI.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Saigon</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1961-09-05">September 5, 1961</date>.</hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>322. Task Force <gloss target="#t_VN1">VN</gloss>. More than 1,000 Viet Cong (two
                    battalions) regular troops attacked and occupied two <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                        >GVN</gloss> posts at Poko and Dakha approximately 50 kilometers north of
                    Kontum on September 1, announced Minister for Civic Action Ngo Trong Hieu at
                    biweekly press conference September 4. According Viet-Nam press, Hieu stated one
                    post retaken by <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> forces. Fighting still going
                    on for second. Also reported 100 <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss>, 19 <gloss
                        target="#t_ARVN1">ARVN</gloss> personnel killed in action so far.</p>
                <p>Hieu said <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> armed with modern weapons and, for
                    first time, wore khaki uniforms into battle.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> If number of <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss>
                    as high as reported, this represents largest <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss>
                    attack to date and possibly result of significant build-up <gloss
                        target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> forces this area recent months. Report of <gloss
                        target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> force being well-armed and uniformed also another
                    possible indication <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> efforts mold guerrilla
                    units into more regular-type forces this region for use against larger <gloss
                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> targets.</p>
                <p>ARMA will report military details this operation.<note n="2" xml:id="d127fn2">The
                        Army Attaché’s report has not been found.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CHF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
